emaiwald@beeblebrox (Eric Maiwald) writes:

>Padgett 0sirius (padgett@141.240.2.145) wrote:
>: Would appreciate it if someone could point me to a factual description of 
>: the encryption used by ccMail. Am told that it is a RSA variant but this 
>: covers a lot of ground. Of particular interest is the following:

>I can't help with the algorithm but I can give you some information on 
>how cc:mail passes messages.  Remember that "messages" are not stored
>or passed between servers, "files" are.  All messages reside in a single
>file on the server and messages that need to move between servers are
>moved as files.

>If I remember correctly, the files on the servers are always encrypted
>and the files are also encrypted in transit.

This is correct. However, I believe cc:Mail is freely exportable--at 
least I don't recall seeing any "North America only" warnings on the 
software. If so, that would restrict the quality of the encryption to 
pretty low-level stuff.


